Comparing Gat201-dependent and Rim101-dependent gene expression

Edward Wallace

2023-04-23

Compare Gat201-dependent and Rim101-dependent gene expression.

Using:

  • RIM101 DEGs in Dulbeccos modified Eagles medium [DMEM] with 5% CO2 at 37C from OMeara et al 2013
  • GAT201 DEGs also in DMEM with 5% CO2 at 37C Homer et al 2016
  • GAT201 DEGs at 4h in RPMI from this study.

Overall, this finds by eyeballing the numbers that there is no evidence for enrichment of RIM101 targets in GAT201 targets or vice versa. This analysis is rough because the datasets are from 3 different studies and analysed in rather different ways. However, in the absence of evidence in favour of overlap from here or elsewhere its a reasonable start.

Also RIM101 is not in the GAT201-dependent list, and vice versa.

Load data, RIM101 and GAT201 in DMEM

  readxl::read_excel("../data_external/OMeara2013_TableS3_Rim101_DEGs_mbo006121415st3.xlsx",

Confirm Gat201 isnt in the RIM101-DEG list and vice versa

"CNAG_01551" %in% RIM101_DEGs_DMEM$gene
## [1] FALSE
"CNAG_05431" %in% dplyr::filter(GAT201_DEGs_DMEM, abs(log2FC_mean) > 1)$gene
## [1] FALSE

Compare RIM101 and GAT201 in DMEM

vennplotdata <- 
  list("RIM101_down" = RIM101_DEGs_DMEM  %>%
         dplyr::filter(lnFC < 0 ) %>%
         dplyr::pull(gene),
         "RIM101_up" = RIM101_DEGs_DMEM  %>%
         dplyr::filter(lnFC > 0 ) %>%
         dplyr::pull(gene),
       "GAT201_up" = GAT201_DEGs_DMEM  %>%
         dplyr::filter(log2FC_mean > 1 ) %>%
         dplyr::pull(gene),
       "GAT201_down" = GAT201_DEGs_DMEM  %>%
         dplyr::filter(log2FC_mean < -1 ) %>%
         dplyr::pull(gene)
  ) %>%
  RVenn::Venn() %>%
  ggVennDiagram::process_data()

venn_RIM101_vs_GAT201_DMEM <- 
  ggplot() +
  geom_sf(aes(color = id), 
          data = ggVennDiagram::venn_setedge(vennplotdata), show.legend = FALSE) +
  geom_sf_text(aes(label = name), 
               data = ggVennDiagram::venn_setlabel(vennplotdata)) +
  geom_sf_text(aes(label = count), 
               data = ggVennDiagram::venn_region(vennplotdata)) +
  theme_void() +
  # scale_colour_manual(values = c("grey20", "darkred", "darkblue")) +
  coord_sf(clip = "off")

venn_RIM101_vs_GAT201_DMEM

Comparing these numbers with the total number of genes (7823 in the GAT201 list) - its clear that there is no statistical enrichment for RIM101 DEGs in GAT201 DEGS or vice versa. No connection.

Compare GAT201 RPMI with GAT201 DMEM

GAT201_down_RPMI4h <- read_lines("../results/DEGids_RPMI4h_vsGAT201_down2x_FDR5.txt")
GAT201_up_RPMI4h <- read_lines("../results/DEGids_RPMI4h_vsGAT201_up2x_FDR5.txt")
vennplotdata <- 
  list("down_RPMI" = GAT201_down_RPMI4h,
       "up_RPMI" = GAT201_up_RPMI4h,
       "up_DMEM" = GAT201_DEGs_DMEM  %>%
         dplyr::filter(log2FC_mean > 1 ) %>%
         dplyr::pull(gene),
       "down_DMEM" = GAT201_DEGs_DMEM  %>%
         dplyr::filter(log2FC_mean < -1 ) %>%
         dplyr::pull(gene)
  ) %>%
  RVenn::Venn() %>%
  ggVennDiagram::process_data()

venn_GAT201_RPMI_vs_GAT201_DMEM <- 
  ggplot() +
  geom_sf(aes(color = id), 
          data = ggVennDiagram::venn_setedge(vennplotdata), show.legend = FALSE) +
  geom_sf_text(aes(label = name), 
               data = ggVennDiagram::venn_setlabel(vennplotdata)) +
  geom_sf_text(aes(label = count), 
               data = ggVennDiagram::venn_region(vennplotdata)) +
  theme_void() +
  # scale_colour_manual(values = c("grey20", "darkred", "darkblue")) +
  coord_sf(clip = "off")

venn_GAT201_RPMI_vs_GAT201_DMEM

This is reasonable. About half the Gat201-regulated genes in RPMI (FDR 5%, 2x enriched) are regulated in the same direction in DMEM (2x mean, no FDR control).

Compare GAT201 RPMI with RIM101 DMEM

vennplotdata <- 
  list("GAT201_RPMI_up" = GAT201_down_RPMI4h,
       "GAT201_RPMI_down" = GAT201_up_RPMI4h,
       "RIM101_DMEM_down" = RIM101_DEGs_DMEM  %>%
         dplyr::filter(lnFC < 0 ) %>%
         dplyr::pull(gene),
       "RIM101_DMEM_up" = RIM101_DEGs_DMEM  %>%
         dplyr::filter(lnFC > 0 ) %>%
         dplyr::pull(gene)
  ) %>%
  RVenn::Venn() %>%
  ggVennDiagram::process_data()

venn_GAT201_RPMI_vs_RIM101_DMEM <- 
  ggplot() +
  geom_sf(aes(color = id), 
          data = ggVennDiagram::venn_setedge(vennplotdata), show.legend = FALSE) +
  geom_sf_text(aes(label = name), 
               data = ggVennDiagram::venn_setlabel(vennplotdata)) +
  geom_sf_text(aes(label = count), 
               data = ggVennDiagram::venn_region(vennplotdata)) +
  theme_void() +
  # scale_colour_manual(values = c("grey20", "darkred", "darkblue")) +
  coord_sf(clip = "off")

venn_GAT201_RPMI_vs_RIM101_DMEM

Again, the overlap is low. I think its low enough that its a waste of time to do any statistical tests to look for more: no evidence for overlapping targets of GAT201 and RIM101.
